name: MOSTLY FILM WORK IN BLACK & WHITE

metadata.name: ALMOST NAILED IT
metadata.description:
Taken back in November of 1998. This is one  of my first official attempts in Photography. 
Why the title? 
Well the stop sign almost overlaps the tree trunk. I thought my angle of view was good and I that I could get it right, but I  missed that lower part of the trunk. 
The idea was to make the octagon look like there were branches all over. I could  have photoshopped it but no, that's the beauty and "ugliness" of film photography. 
Image scanned with a Plustek Opticfilm 8200i Scanner.
